<taxonomicName authorityName="Konow" authorityYear="1897" box="[1011,1123,279,300]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Neurotoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1011,1123,279,300]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Neurotoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p.40 (key), p. 58
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[151,1083,308,330]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
– (aa) Head with lateral sutures subparallel and connected with antennal furrows (
<figureCitation box="[971,1029,308,330]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1aa)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,679,337,359]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(bb) Forewing with vein Sc1 present (
<figureCitation box="[566,623,337,359]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1bb)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,895,367,389]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(cc) Lancet with lamnium small (
<figureCitation box="[524,582,367,389]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="37.[151,250,1614,1638]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1586]" captionTargetId="figure-342@37.[151,1436,918,1590]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURE 1. Key to tribes and genera 1" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876495/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
: 1cc). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1890" box="[646,762,367,389]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="99" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Pamphiliini">Pamphiliini</taxonomicName>
: 3 genera ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[883,895,367,388]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">2</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<keyLead pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[151,192,396,418]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,192,396,418]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">2(1)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,860,425,447]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(a) Crossvein 1r-rs narrowed towards junction with R1 (
<figureCitation box="[753,813,425,447]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,496,455,477]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(b) Legs black (
<figureCitation box="[365,425,455,477]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2b, c).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,1200,484,506]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(c) Hind tibia with two preapical spurs (
<figureCitation box="[598,658,484,506]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2b, c). 1 species, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Takeuchi" baseAuthorityYear="1938" box="[834,993,484,506]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cornaceae" genus="Cornus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cornales" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucocephala">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[834,993,484,506]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">C. leucocephala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1028,1140,484,506]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Chrysolyda</emphasis>
, p. 62
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[151,907,513,535]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
– (aa) Crossvein 1r-rs not narrowed towards junction with R1 (
<figureCitation box="[790,850,513,535]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2aa).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,650,543,565]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(bb) Legs largely pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[496,556,543,565]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2bb, cc).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,805,572,594]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(cc) Hind tibia with three preapical spurs (
<figureCitation box="[610,670,572,594]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 2bb, cc). ... 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[793,805,572,593]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">3</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<keyLead pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[151,191,601,623]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,191,601,623]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">3(2)</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(a) Anterior part of malar space with small, slightly depressed area bearing a row of recurved setae in female, and with large pit containing a long stout seta and several recurved setae in male (
<figureCitation box="[851,911,660,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,1004,689,711]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(b) Male: supraocular area with narrow, dull, densely pubescent patch (
<figureCitation box="[896,956,689,711]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3b).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(c) Tarsal claws with acute basal lobe in addition to apical and one subapical teeth of subequal size (
<figureCitation box="[1176,1236,719,741]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3c). 8 species. ... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Takeuchi" authorityYear="1938" box="[199,318,748,770]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Onycholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,318,748,770]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Onycholyda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 41 (key), p. 62
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
<keyLead pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[151,1285,777,799]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
– (aa) Anterior part of malar space without depressed area or pit bearing recurved setae in both sexes (
<figureCitation box="[1167,1227,777,799]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3aa).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" box="[199,1047,807,829]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(bb) Male: supraocular area without narrow, dull, densely pubescent patch (
<figureCitation box="[927,986,807,829]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3bb).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,220,894]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
(cc) Tarsal claws with apical and one subapical teeth of subequal size and often with rounded basal lobe, but Asian species never with acute basal lobe (
<figureCitation box="[454,514,872,894]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="38.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[164,1422,181,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-26@38.[164,1422,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURE 2. Key to tribes and genera 2" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876497/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
: 3cc). 43 species. ... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1803" box="[712,825,872,894]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[712,825,872,894]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pamphilius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, p. 42 (key), p. 68
</paragraph>
</keyLead>
</keyStep>
